Biography of Famous Chinese Scholar Published
JINAN , December 24 ( Xinhua ) -- The first biography of Ji Xianlin , one of China 's prominent academic figures , was recently published in China by the Shanxi Classics Publishing House .
Its author is Professor Cai Degui of Shandong University .
Ji Xianlin was vice-president of Beijing University and a well-known scholar in modern China .
He is especially accomplished in Oriental literature , Indian studies , and Buddhism .
The 640,000-character book gives a thorough account of Ji 's many experiences from son of a farmer family to prominent scholar and shows the Chinese intellectual 's virtues of patriotism , devotion to work , and diligence .
